    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Templatify gives the ability to select <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/themes/template-files-section/page-template-files/page-templates/#creating-custom-page-templates-for-global-use\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">custom templates</a> for each post type, even custom post types, as for Pages.<br />\nOnce you activate Templatify, a &#8220;Select Template&#8221; box will appear in every post edit screen filled with Pages Templates.</p>\n<p>You can also add post type specific templates: just add &#8220;Template Post Type&#8221; header (similar to &#8220;Template Name&#8221; header for <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/themes/template-files-section/page-template-files/page-templates/#creating-custom-page-templates-for-global-use\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">custom templates</a>) on your custom template to see it in the dropdown selector (see Screenshots).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Author: <a href=\"http://www.marcocanestrari.it/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Marco Canestrari</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the files to the /wp-content/plugins/templatify/ directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.</li>\n<li>Add as many templates as you want, using the &#8220;Template Post Type&#8221; header to set the post type (see Screenshots)</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Sanitized and validated POST calls</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>First release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
    "short_description": "This plugin adds Page Templates feature to Posts and Custom Post Types. No settings needed.",
    "description": "<p>Templatify gives the ability to select <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/themes/template-files-section/page-template-files/page-templates/#creating-custom-page-templates-for-global-use\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">custom templates</a> for each post type, even custom post types, as for Pages.<br />\nOnce you activate Templatify, a &#8220;Select Template&#8221; box will appear in every post edit screen filled with Pages Templates.</p>\n<p>You can also add post type specific templates: just add &#8220;Template Post Type&#8221; header (similar to &#8220;Template Name&#8221; header for <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/themes/template-files-section/page-template-files/page-templates/#creating-custom-page-templates-for-global-use\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">custom templates</a>) on your custom template to see it in the dropdown selector (see Screenshots).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Author: <a href=\"http://www.marcocanestrari.it/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Marco Canestrari</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
